 The Secretary to Kano State Government, Alhaji Usman Alhaji, has declared interest to run for the governorship of the state in the 2023 general elections. He said he wants to succeed Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje as he is part and parcel of the administration. The Wazirin Gaya announced his intention at a dinner organised by the Patriotic Volunteers for Good Governance held in Kano. The SSG also promised to be transparent, honest and conduct affairs of the state with the fear of God. “I intend to build on the good work of Governor Ganduje so that my administration will consolidate just like what is happening in Lagos, Kaduna and Borno states,’’ he said.